DW blaming his costume is a complete embarassment to boxing. An english boxer called Ricky Hatton once rocked up to a big fight in an oversized fat suit as he was getting made fun of outside the ring for putting on weight (and his love of english fast food). Hatton came in confident, back in shape, and won the big fight. Not only that, he went all 12 rounds against an opponent that had him the ropes a few times and rocked him.

I'd bet that Hatton's fat suit was much heavier than DW's costume too. Excuses are for baby-men with no respect for their opponents out-classing them, and they deserve to lose.
